      • readStatsFile

        public static List<Stats> readStatsFile(File statsFile,
                                        int numOfClasses)
                                 throws FileNotFoundException
        Reads the stats file and creates a list of Stats objects to encapsulate the outcomes of learning tasks
        Parameters:
        statsFile - The file in which the stats of the learning tasks were saved
        numOfClasses - The number of classes that the result file contains
        Returns:
        a List of Stats objects, one each for every learning task that was scheduled as a part of the experiment
        Throws:
        FileNotFoundException - If the file supplied does not exist

      • sortList

        public static void sortList(List<Stats> originalList,
                            short byCriteria,
                            boolean descending,
                            Integer classIndex)
        Sorts a List of Stats objects, as per the given metric/field, in either ascending or descending order
        Parameters:
        originalList - The List to sort
        byCriteria - The sort metric/field; should be one of defined constants in Stats class
        descending - If true, sorts the List in decreasing order
        classIndex - The class index, in case the metric is class specific (otherwise ignored)
